quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  80,1,"He [i.e., the Prophet (ﷺ) ] frowned and turned away"
  80,2,"Because there came to him the blind man,{1} [interrupting].",footnotes:1:1
  80,3,"But what would make you perceive, [O Muḥammad], that perhaps he might be purified{1}",footnotes:1:1
  80,4,"Or be reminded and the remembrance would benefit him?"
  80,5,"As for he who thinks himself without need,{1}",footnotes:1:1
  80,6,"To him you give attention."
  80,7,"And not upon you [is any blame] if he will not be purified.{1}",footnotes:1:1
  80,8,"But as for he who came to you striving [for knowledge]"
  80,9,"While he fears [Allāh],"
  80,10,"From him you are distracted."